.\" CSCHOOL(1) Manual Page
.TH CSCHOOL 1 "May 6, 2026" "C-SCHOOL" "C-SCHOOL Manual"
.SH NAME
school \\- C-SCHOOL learning system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B school
[command] [arguments]
.SH DESCRIPTION
school is the primary command interface for C-SCHOOL. 
It provides access to interactive programming lessons.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B school ls
List all available courses.
.TP
.B school cd [course]
Enter a course directory.
.TP
.B school cat [lesson]
Display lesson content.
.TP
.B school vim
Launch vim with C-SCHOOL integration.
.TP
.B school man [topic]
View manual for a topic.
.TP
.B school progress
Show learning progress.
.TP
.B school theme [name]
Change colorscheme.
.TP
.B school timing [percent]
Set animation timing (10-200%).
.SH FILES
.TP
~/c-school/
User home directory for C-SCHOOL.
.TP
~/c-school/profile
User profile data.
.TP
~/c-school/progress.json
Progress tracking.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List courses:
.B school ls
.TP
Start Linux track:
.B school cd linux
.TP
View manual:
.B school man cschool
.SH AUTHORS
C-SCHOOL - A futuristic programming school.
.SH VERSION
C-SCHOOL 1.0
.SH SEE ALSO
cschool(1), man(7)